      <h2 id="how-to-choose">How to actually choose</h2>
      <p>Three questions answer this for almost every climber:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>How many days can you spend on the mountain?</strong> Add the buffer for arrival, briefing, and recovery. If you have 9-10 days on the mountain, take the Northern Circuit. If you have 7-8 days, take Lemosho or the 8-day Machame. If you only have 6 days, take the 7-day Machame and accept the tighter acclimatization. If you only have 5 days, reconsider whether this trip is the right one.</li>
        <li><strong>Are you climbing in the wet season?</strong> If so, choose Rongai or Marangu and avoid the western/southern routes.</li>
        <li><strong>Have you climbed a 4,000 m peak before?</strong> If yes and you specifically want a wilderness experience, Umbwe is on the table. If no, ignore Umbwe.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Once you have answered those, the decision is usually clear. If it isn't, send Nelson your dates and your hiking history. He responds personally within 24 hours.</p>

